# Shopping List

Simple client-side Shopping List app that stores items in Local Storage. Add, edit, remove, clear and filter items in the list.

## Features
- Add new items
- Edit existing items
- Remove single items
- Clear all items
- Live filter of items
- Persist items via Local Storage

## Files
- [index.html](index.html) — main HTML markup.
- [main.js](main.js) — application logic and event handlers.
- [style.css](style.css) — basic styling.
- [.vscode/settings.json](.vscode/settings.json) — Live Server port config.
- [images/](images/) — project images (icons/assets).

## Quick start
1. Open [index.html](index.html) in your browser or use Live Server on port specified in [.vscode/settings.json](.vscode/settings.json) (default: 5501).
2. Type an item into the input and click "Add Item".
3. Click an item to edit it, or click the red X to remove it.
4. Use the "Filter Items" input to search the list.
5. Click "Clear All" to remove all items.

## Key implementation points
- Items are stored as an array in Local Storage under the key `items`.
- Main functions in [main.js](main.js):
  - [`onAddItemSubmit`](main.js) — handles add/update form submissions.
  - [`addItemToDOM`](main.js) — creates and appends a list item element.
  - [`addItemToStorage`](main.js) — persists item to Local Storage.
  - [`getItemsFromStorage`](main.js) — reads items from Local Storage.
  - [`displayItems`](main.js) — renders stored items on load.
  - [`createButton`](main.js) / [`createIcon`](main.js) — helper DOM builders.
  - [`onClickItem`](main.js) — delegates list clicks for edit/remove.
  - [`setItemToEdit`](main.js) — enters edit mode for an item.
  - [`removeItem`](main.js) / [`removeItemFromStorage`](main.js) — remove logic.
  - [`clearItems`](main.js) — clears DOM and Local Storage.
  - [`checkUI`](main.js) — updates button/input visibility.
  - [`filterItems`](main.js) — live filtering.

## Notes & tips
- Duplicate prevention is case-sensitive per current implementation.
- Editing an item removes the old entry from storage and adds the updated text.
- If you want case-insensitive duplicate checking, modify [`checkIfItemExists`](main.js) accordingly.

